main event: A person in Calistoga, California reported sighting an unidentified phenomenon in the sky on February 6, 1969 at 10:00 PM.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 4 minutes.
The observer was asked to indicate the direction and path of the phenomenon on a compass rose diagram and sketch.
The observer was also asked to describe the characteristics of the phenomenon, such as whether it remained steady, moved, changed size or shape, made any sounds, or exhibited other behaviors.
The report notes that the phenomenon was somewhat similar to the planet Venus at the time.
The observer indicated that the phenomenon faded out of sight.
